
Overview of verb indemnify

The verb indemnify has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                    
1. indemnify -- (secure against future loss, damage, or liability; give security for; "This plan indemnifies workers against wages lost through illness")
2. compensate, recompense, repair, indemnify -- (make amends for; pay compensation for; "One can never fully repair the suffering and losses of the Jews in the Third Reich"; "She was compensated for the loss of her arm in the accident")
